This paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on constrained reinforcement learning, which involves optimizing a policy subject to constraints. This topic is closely related to several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Given the focus on reinforcement learning and optimization, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.RO and cs.SY, which are relevant due to the application of these techniques to robotics and control systems. Finally, cs.DS is a possible category due to the use of algorithms and optimization techniques.
